result.execSummary:
Joshua Vernon Price was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Joshua Vernon Price was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Copy of Extradition Consent and Release and Order of Extradition Upon Consent forwarded to Governor Walker, Wisconsin.

Defendant Joshua Vernon Price in court with attorney Roger M Hillestad.  Defendant Joshua Vernon Price in custody.  Jon D Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant confirms he received a copy of Fugitive Complaint.  Warrant out of Wabasha County, Minnesota, Count 1 Assault in Second Degree, Count 2 Theft of a Motor Vehicle, Count 3, Fleeing a Peace Officer.  Court explains Extradition process and advises defendant of rights.  Defendant willing to waive extradition, Atty Hillestad files Extradition Consent & Release with Court.  Court finds defendant's waiver of extradition done knowingly & voluntarily and remands him to Pepin County custody to dorthwith be delivered to accredited agent of the State of Minnesota for return to Wabasha County.
Defendant Joshua Vernon Price in court with attorney Roger M Hillestad.  Defendant in custody.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
